    "text": "Here is a complete, textual inventory of the DFD\u2019s elements, their STRIDE-per\u2011element category, and all labeled connections, plus the trust boundaries.\n\nElements (with STRIDE-per-element category)\n- User (Browser) (External Entity): Human user operating a web browser.\n- Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2) (Process): Web UI that renders pages/templates and exchanges data with backend services.\n- Auth Service (Flask + JWT) (Process): Authentication component that handles login/register and issues/validates JWT or session tokens.\n- Business Logic (Flask) (Process): Core application logic that orchestrates data retrieval, uploads, and AI assistance.\n- Database (PostgreSQL) (Data Store): Relational database used for credentials, transactions, balances, cards, and file metadata.\n- File Upload Handler (Process): Service that receives files, stores binary data, and records metadata.\n- Local File Storage (Data Store): Filesystem or object store used for uploaded binary files.\n- AI Support Agent (Process): Internal service that brokers requests to an external LLM and returns AI assistance to the app.\n- DeepSeek LLM (External Entity): External AI model/service on the public internet.\n\nData flows and connections (direction, name/label)\n- User \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cUser Input\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 User: \u201cOutput\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 Auth Service: \u201cLogin/Register\u201d\n- Auth Service \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cJWT / Session\u201d\n- Auth Service \u2192 Database: \u201cCredentials Check (via SQLAlchemy)\u201d\n- Database \u2192 Auth Service: \u201cValidation Response\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cUser Actions\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cProcessed Results\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 Database: \u201cRequest (Transactions / Balance / Cards via SQLAlchemy)\u201d\n- Database \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cResponse (Transactions / Balance / Cards)\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cFile Upload Request\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cUpload Status / File Metadata\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Local File Storage: \u201cUploaded File (Binary Data)\u201d\n- Local File Storage \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cSave Confirmation\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Database: \u201cFile Metadata Record\u201d\n- Database \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cInsert Confirmation / Stored Metadata\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 AI Support Agent: \u201cAI Assistance Request\u201d\n- AI Support Agent \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cAI Assistance Response\u201d\n- AI Support Agent \u2192 DeepSeek LLM: \u201cAI Query Request\u201d\n- DeepSeek LLM \u2192 AI Support Agent: \u201cAI Response\u201d\n\nTrust boundaries (not classified as elements)\n- AppContainer Boundary: Encloses all in-app components and storage: Frontend UI, Auth Service, Business Logic, Database, File Upload Handler, Local File Storage, and AI Support Agent. Flows crossing into/out of this boundary include traffic from the User (Browser) to the Frontend UI and traffic from the AI Support Agent to the external DeepSeek LLM.\n- Internet Boundary: Encloses the external DeepSeek LLM service. The \u201cAI Query Request\u201d and \u201cAI Response\u201d flows cross between the AppContainer Boundary and the Internet Boundary.",
    "valid_mistakes": [],
