        {
            "role": "system",
            "content": "# Role and Objective\n\nYou are a **Threat Modeling expert** with 20 years of experience.\n\n## Your objectives are:\n- to provide user with relative information about cybersecurity threats;\n- to describe ways of mitigation for those threats;\n- to analyze user's systems and compile reports about threats within those systems;\n- to answer user questions regarding those reports.\n\n# Instructions\n- Always follow the provided output format for new messages.\n- Maintain a professional and concise tone in all responses.\n- Rely on data provided with the user's message whenever appropriate. Especially if it contains information regarding cybersecurity threats, mitigations, etc.\n- If you've resolved the user's request, ask if there's anything else you can help with.\n\n## Report generation\nWhen provided with the system description and report output format, think step-by-step:\n1. Analyze the provided system description.\n2. Perform comprehensive threat modeling according to the frameworks described lower.\n3. If you reach a limit of the response size and there is the **is_final** field in the provided output format, fill it with **False** to indicate that the report is incomplete.\n4. When asked to **CONTINUE**, carry on with the report. In this case use the message field for additional thinking.\n\n- Always identify ALL possible threats.\n- Multiple instances of the same threat type can exist across different system elements and connections.\n- Sometimes not all OWASP or MITRE threats may be present in the system.\n- Avoid generation of non-applicable threats.\n- List every threat separately for different elements, explain their specific context and risk level for that particular element.\n- Consider how threats affect both system components and their interactions (connections, APIs, data flows, etc.)\n- Always fill all the necessary fields unless otherwise stated.\n\n# Output Format\n- Use the following format for OWASP and MITRE threats:\n    **`<ThreatID>: <ThreatName>`**\n    For example:\n    - **LLM01: Prompt Injection**\n    - **AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection**\n\n# Threat model context\nUse the following threats for the corresponding threat models:\n\n\n## STRIDE:\nWhile generating threats use **STRIDE-per-Element** approach. Each element **must** contain threats according to the matrix, so fully cover it with relevant threats.\n\n### STRIDE Matrix:\nMatrix contains appropriate threat types for each element type.\nExternal Entity: Spoofing, Repudiation\nProcess: Spoofing, Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service, Elevation of Privileges\nData Flow: Tampering, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service\nData Store: Tampering, Repudiation, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service## OWASP Top 10 for LLM 2025:\nLLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection - Manipulating LLMs via crafted inputs can lead to unauthorized access, data breaches, and compromised decision-making.\nLLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure - Failure to protect against disclosure of sensitive information in LLM outputs can result in legal consequences or a loss of competitive advantage.\nLLM03: 2025 Supply Chain - Depending upon compromised components, services or datasets undermine system integrity, causing data breaches and system failures.\nLLM04: Data and Model Poisoning - Manipulating training, fine-tuning, or embedding data introduces vulnerabilities, backdoors, or biases that degrade model security, performance, and ethical behavior.\nLLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling - Neglecting to validate LLM outputs may lead to downstream security exploits, including code execution that compromises systems and exposes data.\nLLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency - Granting LLMs unchecked autonomy to take action can lead to unintended consequences, jeopardizing reliability, privacy, and trust.\nLLM07: 2025 System Prompt Leakage - Exposing system prompts can reveal sensitive information, such as credentials or security controls, leading to potential attacks.\nLLM08: 2025 Vector and Embedding Weaknesses - Insecure handling of vectors and embeddings in Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) systems can lead to data poisoning, model manipulation, and unauthorized access.\nLLM09: 2025 Misinformation - LLMs can generate false or misleading information that appears credible, leading to security risks, reputational damage, and legal liability.\nLLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption - Allowing excessive and uncontrolled LLM inferences can lead to denial of service (DoS), financial loss, model theft, and service degradation.## MITRE ATLAS:\nAML.T0000: Search for Victim's Publicly Available Research Materials - Adversaries may search publicly available research to learn how and where machine learning is used within a victim organization.\nAML.T0001: Search for Publicly Available Adversarial Vulnerability Analysis - An adversary will likely try to identify any pre-existing researches available on the vulnerabilities that has been done for this class of models.\nAML.T0002: Acquire Public ML Artifacts - Adversaries may search public sources for machine learning artifacts, including software stacks, datasets, and model configurations.\nAML.T0003: Search Victim-Owned Websites - Adversaries may search victim-owned websites for technical details, organizational information, key employee data, and business operations to aid in targeting.\nAML.T0004: Search Application Repositories - Adversaries may search open application repositories, such as Google Play and the App Store, for targeting information.\nAML.T0005: Create Proxy ML Model - Adversaries may obtain proxy models to simulate full offline access to the victim's target model.\nAML.T0006: Active Scanning - Adversaries may probe or scan victim systems for targeting, involving direct interaction unlike other reconnaissance methods.\nAML.T0007: Discover ML Artifacts - Adversaries may search private sources for machine learning artifacts, such as software stacks and data repositories, to refine attacks and identify targets for exfiltration or disruption.\nAML.T0008: Acquire Infrastructure - Adversaries may acquire or rent various infrastructure, including servers, domains, and web services, to support their operations.\nAML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise - Adversaries may gain initial access by compromising the ML supply chain, sometimes requiring secondary access to complete their attack.\nAML.T0011: User Execution - An adversary may rely upon specific actions by a user in order to gain execution.\nAML.T0012: Valid Accounts - Adversaries may obtain and abuse credentials of existing accounts as a means of gaining Initial Access.\nAML.T0013: Discover ML Model Ontology - Adversaries may discover the ontology of a machine learning model's output space, for example, the types of objects a model can detect.\nAML.T0014: Discover ML Model Family - Adversaries may discover the general family of model.\nAML.T0015: Evade ML Model - Adversaries can craft adversarial data that prevent a machine learning model from correctly identifying the contents of the data.\nAML.T0016: Obtain Capabilities - Adversaries may search for and obtain software capabilities for use in their operations.\nAML.T0017: Develop Capabilities - Adversaries may develop their own capabilities to support operations. This process encompasses identifying requirements, building solutions, and deploying capabilities.\nAML.T0018: Backdoor ML Model - Adversaries may implant backdoors in ML models, causing them to behave normally but produce adversary-controlled outputs when triggered.\nAML.T0019: Publish Poisoned Datasets - Adversaries may poison training data and publish it to a public location.\nAML.T0020: Poison Training Data - Adversaries may attempt to poison datasets used by a ML model by modifying the underlying data or its labels.\nAML.T0021: Establish Accounts - Adversaries may create accounts with various services for use in targeting, to gain access to resources needed in ML Attack Staging, or for victim impersonation.\nAML.T0024: Exfiltration via ML Inference API - Adversaries may exfiltrate private information via ML Model Inference API Access.\nAML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means - Adversaries may exfiltrate ML artifacts or other information relevant to their goals via traditional cyber means.\nAML.T0029: Denial of ML Service - Adversaries may target machine learning systems with a flood of requests for the purpose of degrading or shutting down the service.\nAML.T0031: Erode ML Model Integrity - Adversaries may degrade the target model's performance with adversarial data inputs to erode confidence in the system over time.\nAML.T0034: Cost Harvesting - Adversaries may target different machine learning services to send useless queries or computationally expensive inputs to increase the cost of running services at the victim organization.\nAML.T0035: ML Artifact Collection - Adversaries may collect ML artifacts, such as models, datasets, and telemetry data, for Exfiltration or for use in ML Attack Staging.\nAML.T0036: Data from Information Repositories - Adversaries may leverage information repositories to mine valuable information.\nAML.T0037: Data from Local System - Adversaries may search local system sources, such as file systems and configuration files or local databases, to find files of interest and sensitive data prior to Exfiltration.\nAML.T0040: ML Model Inference API Access - Adversaries may gain access to a model via legitimate access to the inference API to Discover ML Model Ontology, Model Family, to Verify Attack, Craft Adversarial Data, Evade ML Model, Erode ML Model Integrity.\nAML.T0041: Physical Environment Access - If the model is interacting with data collected from the real world in some way, the adversary can influence the model through access to wherever the data is being collected.\nAML.T0042: Verify Attack - Adversaries can verify the efficacy of their attack via an inference API or access to an offline copy of the target model.\nAML.T0043: Craft Adversarial Data - Adversarial data are inputs to a machine learning model that have been modified such that they cause the adversary's desired effect in the target model.\nAML.T0044: Full ML Model Access - Adversaries may gain full \"white-box\" access to a machine learning model, including its architecture, parameters, and class ontology.\nAML.T0046: Spamming ML System with Chaff Data - Adversaries may flood the ML system with chaff data, increasing detections and causing analysts to waste time on incorrect inferences.\nAML.T0047: ML-Enabled Product or Service - Adversaries may use a product or service that uses machine learning under the hood to gain access to the underlying machine learning model.\nAML.T0048: External Harms - Adversaries may abuse their access to a victim system and use its resources or capabilities to further their goals by causing harms external to that system.\nAML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application - Adversaries may exploit weaknesses in internet-facing systems, such as bugs or design flaws, to induce unintended behavior.\nAML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter - Adversaries may abuse command and script interpreters to execute commands, scripts, or binaries.\nAML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection - An adversary may craft malicious prompts as inputs to an LLM that cause the LLM to act in unintended ways.\nAML.T0052: Phishing - Adversaries may send phishing messages to gain access to victim systems.\nAML.T0053: LLM Plugin Compromise - Adversaries may use their access to an LLM that is part of a larger system to compromise connected plugins.\nAML.T0054: LLM Jailbreak - An adversary may use a carefully crafted LLM Prompt Injection designed to place LLM in a state in which it will freely respond to any user input, bypassing any controls, restrictions, or guardrails placed on the LLM.\nAML.T0055: Unsecured Credentials - Adversaries may search compromised systems to find and obtain insecurely stored credentials.\nAML.T0056: LLM Meta Prompt Extraction - An adversary may induce an LLM to reveal its initial instructions, or \"meta prompt\" and get sensitive information about the internal workings of the system.\nAML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage - Adversaries may craft prompts that induce the LLM to leak sensitive information. This can include private user data or proprietary information.\n\n\n\n# Reasoning Steps\nFirst, think carefully step by step about the user's system, elements, connections and applicable threats. Then, construct a report."
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "Here is a complete, textual inventory of the DFD\u2019s elements, their STRIDE-per\u2011element category, and all labeled connections, plus the trust boundaries.\n\nElements (with STRIDE-per-element category)\n- User (Browser) (External Entity): Human user operating a web browser.\n- Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2) (Process): Web UI that renders pages/templates and exchanges data with backend services.\n- Auth Service (Flask + JWT) (Process): Authentication component that handles login/register and issues/validates JWT or session tokens.\n- Business Logic (Flask) (Process): Core application logic that orchestrates data retrieval, uploads, and AI assistance.\n- Database (PostgreSQL) (Data Store): Relational database used for credentials, transactions, balances, cards, and file metadata.\n- File Upload Handler (Process): Service that receives files, stores binary data, and records metadata.\n- Local File Storage (Data Store): Filesystem or object store used for uploaded binary files.\n- AI Support Agent (Process): Internal service that brokers requests to an external LLM and returns AI assistance to the app.\n- DeepSeek LLM (External Entity): External AI model/service on the public internet.\n\nData flows and connections (direction, name/label)\n- User \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cUser Input\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 User: \u201cOutput\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 Auth Service: \u201cLogin/Register\u201d\n- Auth Service \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cJWT / Session\u201d\n- Auth Service \u2192 Database: \u201cCredentials Check (via SQLAlchemy)\u201d\n- Database \u2192 Auth Service: \u201cValidation Response\u201d\n- Frontend UI \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cUser Actions\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 Frontend UI: \u201cProcessed Results\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 Database: \u201cRequest (Transactions / Balance / Cards via SQLAlchemy)\u201d\n- Database \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cResponse (Transactions / Balance / Cards)\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cFile Upload Request\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cUpload Status / File Metadata\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Local File Storage: \u201cUploaded File (Binary Data)\u201d\n- Local File Storage \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cSave Confirmation\u201d\n- File Upload Handler \u2192 Database: \u201cFile Metadata Record\u201d\n- Database \u2192 File Upload Handler: \u201cInsert Confirmation / Stored Metadata\u201d\n- Business Logic \u2192 AI Support Agent: \u201cAI Assistance Request\u201d\n- AI Support Agent \u2192 Business Logic: \u201cAI Assistance Response\u201d\n- AI Support Agent \u2192 DeepSeek LLM: \u201cAI Query Request\u201d\n- DeepSeek LLM \u2192 AI Support Agent: \u201cAI Response\u201d\n\nTrust boundaries (not classified as elements)\n- AppContainer Boundary: Encloses all in-app components and storage: Frontend UI, Auth Service, Business Logic, Database, File Upload Handler, Local File Storage, and AI Support Agent. Flows crossing into/out of this boundary include traffic from the User (Browser) to the Frontend UI and traffic from the AI Support Agent to the external DeepSeek LLM.\n- Internet Boundary: Encloses the external DeepSeek LLM service. The \u201cAI Query Request\u201d and \u201cAI Response\u201d flows cross between the AppContainer Boundary and the Internet Boundary."
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Approach: I applied STRIDE-per-Element and mapped relevant MITRE ATLAS and OWASP Top 10 for LLM 2025 where applicable, focusing on components, their responsibilities, and trust boundary crossings (User\u2194AppContainer and AI Support Agent\u2194DeepSeek over the Internet). Assumptions: standard Flask deployment behind a reverse proxy, PostgreSQL reachable over an internal network, Local File Storage mounted or accessed via internal service endpoint, and AI Support Agent communicates with DeepSeek via HTTPS and API keys. Scope of this part: element-level threats only (External Entities, Processes, Data Stores). I will cover all data flow threats next. Mitigations emphasize authentication/authorization, secure-by-default frameworks, least privilege, strong crypto/TLS, input/output validation, logging with tamper-evidence, and operational protections (rate limiting, isolation, monitoring).\\n\\nIf you\u2019d like, I can continue with the 3 STRIDE threats (Tampering/Info Disclosure/DoS) for each of the 20 data flows crossing the boundaries and internal services.\", \"threats\": [{\"id\": 1, \"element\": \"User (Browser)\", \"threat_description\": \"Attacker spoofs a legitimate user via stolen credentials/session (credential stuffing/phishing) to access accounts.\", \"element_type\": \"External Entity\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0012: Valid Accounts\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enforce MFA; detect and block credential stuffing with rate limits/bot detection; short-lived, rotated session tokens; device binding and re-auth for sensitive actions; session revocation on anomaly.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 2, \"element\": \"User (Browser)\", \"threat_description\": \"Users can deny having initiated transactions or requests due to insufficient non-repudiation/audit evidence.\", \"element_type\": \"External Entity\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Maintain tamper-evident, time-synced audit logs capturing user ID, IP/device fingerprint, request IDs; digitally sign critical requests/receipts; show confirmation screens and email receipts.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 3, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"Session hijacking/fixation or missing CSRF protections allow acting as another user.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite=strict cookies; rotate session IDs on login; enforce CSRF tokens; strict origin/referrer checks; JWT audience/issuer/nonce checks.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 4, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) or other input tampering leading to code execution.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enable autoescape; never render user-controlled template strings; use Jinja2 sandboxed environment; rigorous input validation/encoding; dependency patching; WAF rules.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 5, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"Insufficient request/response/audit logging enables denial of actions by users without traceability.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Structured, immutable logs with user/session IDs and request IDs; time sync; write-once or tamper-evident storage; log integrity monitoring.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 6, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"XSS, verbose errors, or misconfigured caching discloses sensitive data.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Strict CSP; output encoding; avoid reflecting user input; redact errors; disable client caching of sensitive data; secure headers; template autoescape.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 7, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"Request floods or slowloris exhaust front-end resources.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"WAF, rate limiting, connection timeouts, keep-alive and header size limits, autoscaling/CDN, request body size limits.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 8, \"element\": \"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\", \"threat_description\": \"Template or deserialization flaws enable code execution and privilege escalation on the host.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Elevation of Privileges\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Disable dangerous Jinja2 features; no untrusted deserialization; run as non-root with seccomp/AppArmor; container isolation; least OS/file permissions.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 9, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"JWT forgery/replay (weak secrets, alg=none, missing audience/expiry) allows impersonation.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Use strong signing (RS256/ES256), verify alg, iss/aud/exp/nbf, jti with replay cache; rotate keys; short TTL; TLS everywhere.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 10, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"Tampering via SQL injection during credential checks or JWT tampering in transit.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Parameterize queries via SQLAlchemy; least-privileged DB roles; strict JWT verification; mTLS between services; input validation.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 11, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"Insufficient login/token issuance logging enables denial of actions and hinders forensics.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Log auth attempts, token issuance/refresh/revocations; correlate with IP/device; store tamper-evidently; alert on anomalies.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 12, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"User enumeration or token/credential leakage via verbose errors or logs.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Generic authentication errors; avoid logging secrets; minimize JWT claims; encrypt secrets at rest; secure config.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 13, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"Brute-force/password spraying and expensive hashing lead to service exhaustion.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Rate limits, CAPTCHA/bot detection, exponential backoff, IP reputation; tune Argon2/bcrypt cost and use adaptive throttling.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 14, \"element\": \"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\", \"threat_description\": \"Privilege escalation via missing authorization on admin or token scope confusion.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Elevation of Privileges\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enforce RBAC/ABAC; validate scopes on every call; default-deny; separate admin surface; security tests for IDOR and scope bypass.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 15, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"Endpoints trust asserted identity (missing JWT verification), allowing impersonation.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Verify JWT signature and claims server-side; enforce session binding; check CSRF on state-changing operations.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 16, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"Parameter tampering (amounts, IDs) enables fraudulent transactions or metadata corruption.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Server-side validation; enforce object-level auth; idempotency keys; HMAC-signed intents; double-entry checks for funds moves.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 17, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"Insufficient transaction/audit logging lets users repudiate actions.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Append-only audit trails with request IDs and cryptographic integrity; secure time source; regular log integrity verification.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 18, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"IDOR/over-broad queries disclose other users\u2019 transactions/cards.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enforce object- and field-level authorization; tenant scoping; parameterized queries; avoid over-fetching; response filtering.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 19, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"Expensive queries/report generation cause CPU/DB exhaustion.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Request quotas; pagination; query timeouts/limits; caching; circuit breakers; backpressure.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 20, \"element\": \"Business Logic (Flask)\", \"threat_description\": \"Unsafe eval/deserialization or command execution leads to privilege escalation/RCE.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Elevation of Privileges\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Avoid eval/exec; no untrusted deserialization; sandbox risky libraries; run with least OS privileges; egress filtering.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 21, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Unauthenticated or mis-scoped upload endpoints allow identity spoofing or cross-tenant writes.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Require auth/authorization on upload; use presigned URLs with short TTL and scope; bind uploads to user/session IDs.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 22, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Path traversal, filename collisions, or malicious file contents tamper with stored data/system.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Normalize/whitelist paths; randomize names; AV/malware scanning; block dangerous types; store outside webroot; checksum verification.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 23, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Lack of upload event logging allows repudiation or inability to trace file origin.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Record uploader identity, timestamps, source IP, file hashes and metadata; store in tamper-evident logs.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 24, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Serving files without authorization or leaking metadata exposes sensitive content.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Private storage; enforce authorization on downloads; presigned short-lived URLs; do not inline sensitive files; encrypt at rest.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 25, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Oversized uploads, zip bombs, or many concurrent uploads exhaust resources.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Max size limits; streaming uploads; concurrency caps; content inspection; timeouts; detect compression bombs before extraction.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 26, \"element\": \"File Upload Handler\", \"threat_description\": \"Vulnerable file parsers (e.g., image/PDF processing) enable code execution and privilege escalation.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Elevation of Privileges\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Use patched libraries; isolate processing in sandbox/container with seccomp/AppArmor; drop privileges; limit syscalls and egress.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 27, \"element\": \"Database (PostgreSQL)\", \"threat_description\": \"Data tampering via SQL injection or compromised DB credentials.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Strict ORM parameterization; least-privileged roles; separate read/write users; change control; DB ACLs.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 28, \"element\": \"Database (PostgreSQL)\", \"threat_description\": \"Lack of immutable audit trails allows repudiation of DB changes.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enable pg_audit; append-only audit schema; WAL archiving; cryptographic log sealing and offsite replication.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 29, \"element\": \"Database (PostgreSQL)\", \"threat_description\": \"Sensitive data exposure via misconfigurations, backups, or snapshot leaks.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Encrypt at rest and in transit; restrict backup access; row-level security; data masking; secrets management.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 30, \"element\": \"Database (PostgreSQL)\", \"threat_description\": \"DB resource exhaustion (locks, long-running queries) causing service degradation.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Connection pooling; query timeouts; statement time limits; indexes; load shedding; monitoring and auto-kill of runaway queries.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 31, \"element\": \"Local File Storage\", \"threat_description\": \"Files altered or deleted (ransomware/insider) corrupting content.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Immutable/WORM or versioned storage; checksums; restricted service accounts; signed writes; backup/restore testing.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 32, \"element\": \"Local File Storage\", \"threat_description\": \"No provenance/versioning allows repudiation of file changes.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Enable object versioning; maintain write logs with hashes and timestamps; tamper-evident storage.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 33, \"element\": \"Local File Storage\", \"threat_description\": \"Publicly exposed storage paths or weak ACLs leak uploaded files.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Private buckets/paths; deny-by-default ACLs; encrypt at rest; no direct public links; presigned short-lived URLs for access.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 34, \"element\": \"Local File Storage\", \"threat_description\": \"Storage exhaustion or I/O saturation prevents reads/writes.\", \"element_type\": \"Data Store\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Quotas; lifecycle policies; monitoring/alerts; separate hot/cold tiers; autoscaling and backpressure.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 35, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Impersonation of downstream LLM endpoint or caller identity leads to unauthorized access/actions.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0040: ML Model Inference API Access\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM03: 2025 Supply Chain\", \"mitigation\": \"mTLS with certificate pinning to provider; domain allowlists/DNSSEC; request signing; workload identity for outbound calls; strict inbound authn/z.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 36, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Prompt injection via user-controlled inputs causes the agent to exfiltrate data or perform unsafe actions.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Tampering\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\", \"mitigation\": \"Input isolation and schema validation; content/URL allowlists; retrieval/attachment sanitization; instruction hierarchy and output filters; tool/function allowlists.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 37, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Lack of prompt/response/tool-use logging enables repudiation and hinders incident response.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": null, \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\", \"mitigation\": \"Structured logs linking user, context, prompts, responses, and tool calls; PII minimization/redaction; tamper-evident storage; retention policies.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 38, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Sensitive information disclosure in prompts or outputs, including system prompt leakage.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Information Disclosure\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\", \"mitigation\": \"PII scrubbing/redaction; never include secrets in prompts; encrypt context at rest/in transit; detect and block leakage; mask system prompts; retrieval access controls.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"}, {\"id\": 39, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Unbounded LLM calls or large contexts cause cost blowups or service exhaustion.\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Denial of Service\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\", \"mitigation\": \"Per-user/org quotas; rate limits; circuit breakers; response caching; max tokens/context; upstream budget caps and alerts.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}, {\"id\": 40, \"element\": \"AI Support Agent\", \"threat_description\": \"Excessive agency or insecure tool plugins allow escalation to privileged actions (confused-deputy).\", \"element_type\": \"Process\", \"stride\": \"Elevation of Privileges\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0053: LLM Plugin Compromise\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\", \"mitigation\": \"Capability sandboxing; explicit allowlists; human-in-the-loop for high-risk actions; per-tool scopes/guardrails; egress and secret access controls.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 41, \"element\": \"DeepSeek LLM\", \"threat_description\": \"Spoofed provider endpoint or SDK/update compromise leads to adversary-controlled responses.\", \"element_type\": \"External Entity\", \"stride\": \"Spoofing\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": \"LLM03: 2025 Supply Chain\", \"mitigation\": \"Use official SDKs with signature verification; pin TLS certificates; verify domains; monitor SBOM/attestations; restrict outbound to allowlisted hosts.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"}, {\"id\": 42, \"element\": \"DeepSeek LLM\", \"threat_description\": \"Provider denies generating a harmful output or request receipt due to lack of traceability.\", \"element_type\": \"External Entity\", \"stride\": \"Repudiation\", \"mitre_atlas\": \"AML.T0042: Verify Attack\", \"owasp_top_10_for_llm\": null, \"mitigation\": \"Capture request IDs, timestamps, hashes of prompts/responses; enable provider-side logging/correlation; contractual SLAs for auditability.\", \"cvss_vector\": \"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N\"}], \"is_final\": false}"
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "**CONTINUE**"
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Continuing: covering STRIDE for all Data Flows (Tampering, Information Disclosure, Denial of Service), with added OWASP LLM 2025 and MITRE ATLAS where applicable, especially on flows crossing the AppContainer and Internet boundaries. Mitigations emphasize TLS/mTLS, signing, least privilege, strict validation, quotas/rate limits, output handling, and logging. This completes the model. If you want prioritization (e.g., by risk) or a controls roadmap mapped to NIST/ISO/OWASP-ASVS, I can add that next.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":43,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Request tampering/MITM or client-side manipulation of parameters and CSRF leading to unauthorized actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS 1.3 + HSTS; CSRF tokens; server-side validation/authorization; avoid sensitive data in URLs; integrity/checksums for critical intents.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":44,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Sniffing or leakage of credentials/PII via insecure transport, referer headers, or browser cache.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce TLS/HSTS; secure headers (Referrer-Policy=no-referrer, Cache-Control=no-store); avoid PII in query strings; input redaction in logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":45,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Request floods or large bodies overwhelm front-end and upstream services.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"WAF/rate limits; request body size/time limits; bot detection; CDN shielding; connection throttling/backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":46,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering/MITM or content injection modifies outputs (e.g., malicious JS).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS/HSTS; strong CSP; subresource integrity; avoid inline scripts; response signing where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":47,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data exposed in responses or via client/proxy caching and verbose errors.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Minimize sensitive fields; redact errors; Cache-Control: no-store; X-Content-Type-Options; avoid exposing internal IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":48,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Large/streaming responses and downloads saturate client/network, amplifying DoS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-response size/time limits; pagination/chunking; compression and rate limits; abort slow clients.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":49,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with login/register payloads or MITM on internal hop alters auth decisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS/service mesh; request signing; strict schema validation; replay protection (nonce/jti).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":50,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Credentials or PII disclosure over the wire or through logs/metrics.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; minimize/avoid transmitting secrets; redact logs; secure metrics; OAuth best practices.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":51,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst of auth requests exhausts the service on this path.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-IP/user rate limits at edge; CAPTCHA; circuit breakers; priority queues for authenticated traffic.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":52,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token/session tampering or swap in transit (e.g., man-in-the-middle inside cluster).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; Set-Cookie with HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite=strict; sign tokens (RS/ES); bind token to client context where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":53,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token/session disclosure via headers, referrers, or improper storage.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not place tokens in URLs; HttpOnly cookies; Referrer-Policy: no-referrer; avoid localStorage for secrets; short TTL.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":54,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token refresh/issuance bursts overwhelm channels or caches.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Throttle token issuance; exponential backoff; cache headers; staggered refresh; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":55,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with DB connection/queries in transit (downgraded TLS, MITM).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce TLS to DB with cert validation; restrict network paths; parameterized queries; least-privileged DB user.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":56,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of credentials or password hashes during auth checks.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; avoid SELECTing sensitive columns; hash-and-compare within DB function; encrypt columns; protect backups/snapshots.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":57,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Auth check bursts exhaust DB connections or locks.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Connection pooling; rate limit login attempts; statement_timeout; caching of safe-to-cache metadata.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":58,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Validation responses altered in transit causing incorrect auth results.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; response schema validation; check row counts/expected flags; replay protection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":59,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of unnecessary columns in responses (e.g., password hashes, salts).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Principle of least data; views/stored procedures; column-level encryption/masking; avoid logging result sets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":60,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Slow/large responses tie up threads and block auth pipeline.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Query optimization; pagination; timeouts; circuit breaker fallback to \u2018temporarily unavailable\u2019.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":61,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Parameter tampering or JWT misuse in transit leads to unauthorized actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; verify JWTs; server-side validation; idempotency keys for state changes; signed requests for critical actions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":62,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Leakage of PII or account identifiers via headers, URLs, or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; avoid PII in URL; structured logging with redaction; encrypt sensitive request fields end-to-end where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":63,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"High rate of state-changing actions overwhelms business logic.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-user/org quotas; rate limiting; asynchronous job offloading; backpressure/circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":64,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering in transit could alter balances/transactions shown.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; signed data for critical reads; ETag integrity; client-side verification for critical displays if applicable.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":65,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Over-broad data in responses discloses other users\u2019 info (multi-tenant leakage).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Data minimization; object/tenant scoping; response filtering; schema-based serializers with allowlists.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":66,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Very large responses or server-sent events overwhelm clients and infrastructure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pagination; max response size and time; streaming with backpressure; per-client rate limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":67,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with SQL traffic or parameters over the network leads to incorrect writes/reads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS to DB; prepared statements; role separation; firewall rules limiting DB access to service IPs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":68,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of sensitive query parameters or embedded secrets (e.g., in DSNs).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Secrets manager for DSNs; TLS; minimize PII in queries; log redaction; encrypt sensitive columns.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":69,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Query storms or long transactions overload DB via this path.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Statement timeouts; connection pool limits; caching; rate limits; circuit breakers/fail fast.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":70,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered result sets (MITM) or stale replays lead to incorrect business decisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; response verification (row counts, checksums); reject unexpected schemas; use transaction IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":71,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Excess or sensitive fields returned leak PII/PCI data to app and logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Views/whitelists; row/column-level security; data masking; restrict ORM eager loading; log redaction.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":72,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Huge result sets overwhelm app memory/threads causing cascade failures.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"LIMIT/pagination; server-side cursors; memory limits; streaming with backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":73,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with upload metadata (e.g., content-type, filename) changes downstream handling.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strict schema; sanitize filenames; sign metadata (HMAC) with request; enforce server-detected MIME types.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":74,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of sensitive metadata (filenames, paths, user IDs) during upload initiation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; minimize metadata; avoid embedding PII in names; log redaction; encrypt sensitive metadata fields in transit and at rest.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":75,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Oversized or too many concurrent upload requests overwhelm the handler.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Max body size; streaming; concurrency caps; per-user quotas; pre-signed URL expirations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":76,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Status/metadata tampering (e.g., false success) misleads business logic.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; signed callbacks with shared keys; correlate with server-side computed hashes and sizes; idempotency tokens.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":77,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Metadata responses leak sensitive attributes (owner IDs, internal paths).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Minimize response fields; mask IDs; access checks before returning metadata; log redaction.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":78,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst of callback/status messages overloads business logic message handlers.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limiting; queueing with backpressure; collapse duplicate callbacks; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":79,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering of binary data or headers in transit to storage (e.g., NFS/S3 MITM).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS to object store; server-side encryption with customer-managed keys; checksum/ETag verification; signed URLs with short TTL.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":80,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of file contents or keys during upload (e.g., misconfigured bucket, sniffing).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private buckets/shares; TLS; server-side encryption; tight IAM; disable public ACLs; VPC endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":81,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"High-rate or large uploads saturate storage bandwidth/IO.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-tenant quotas; bandwidth throttling; multipart/chunked uploads with limits; lifecycle policies to free space.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":82,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered confirmations (e.g., fake ETag) or replays mislead about write success.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; verify ETag/checksum vs. local hash; ensure strong consistency or read-after-write checks; nonce-based replay protection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":83,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Path, bucket, or internal IDs exposed in confirmations/logs leak structure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Return opaque IDs; avoid logging full paths; encrypt sensitive metadata; strict IAM to prevent listing.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":84,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Delayed or streaming confirmations hold connections open and exhaust handler threads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Async callbacks; timeouts; bounded thread pools; bulk confirmations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":85,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with metadata inserts or parameters in transit to DB.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; prepared statements; input normalization; least-privilege DB role for writes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":86,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive metadata (PII, file hashes) exposed during insert or in logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; encrypt sensitive columns; minimize stored metadata; redaction; access controls on logs/backups.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":87,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"High-volume insert traffic saturates DB write capacity.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Batching; async queues; write quotas; partitioning/indexing; circuit breakers on spikes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":88,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered insert confirmations cause inconsistent application state.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; verify row counts/IDs; idempotent operations; compare echoed values with request.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":89,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of internal keys/paths or unrelated rows in confirmation payloads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Views limiting columns; DTO/serializer allowlists; masking; logging hygiene.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":90,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Slow confirmations/backpressure cause upload handler thread starvation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Timeouts; async processing; bounded queues; fallback retries with jitter.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:M/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":91,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompt injection rides along user context to alter downstream agent instructions/actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Isolate untrusted content; instruction hierarchy; input schema and content filters; tool/function allowlists; strip/escape model-affecting tokens in content.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":92,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data or system prompts included in context leak to the agent and potentially to the model/provider.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Redact/minimize context; never include secrets; role-based retrieval; mask/rotate system prompts; encrypt sensitive context at rest/in transit.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":93,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Huge contexts or high request rate overwhelm the agent pipeline and budgets.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Max tokens/context; per-user quotas; circuit breakers; deduplication/caching; admission control.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":94,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering or tool-use injection embedded in model outputs leads to unsafe downstream actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Treat outputs as untrusted; schema/regex validators; require human-in-the-loop for high-risk actions; allowlist tools; strip control tokens.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":95,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"AI responses may contain sensitive data or system instructions that leak when logged or shown.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"PII redaction before logging/display; classify and filter outputs; least-privilege access to logs/telemetry; data retention limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":96,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Large outputs or streaming tokens overwhelm parsers/UI and backend resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Max tokens in response; streaming with backpressure; timeouts; chunk validation and truncation; rate limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":97,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"MITM/tampering of AI requests alters prompts, tools, or parameters across the Internet boundary.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0040: ML Model Inference API Access\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM03: 2025 Supply Chain\",\"mitigation\":\"TLS 1.3 with cert pinning; DNSSEC/DoH; egress allowlists; request signing and nonce; verify provider hostnames.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":98,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"PII/secrets in prompts exfiltrated to provider via inference API.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0024: Exfiltration via ML Inference API\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Data minimization/redaction; per-tenant consent and DPA; encrypt prompts in transit; segregate contexts; use provider data controls (no-train flags).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":99,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst or expensive requests (long contexts/high compute) cause DoS/cost blowouts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Token and RPM quotas; budget caps and alerts; exponential backoff with jitter; cache identical prompts; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"},{\"id\":100,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering/replay of AI responses or upstream gateway injection alters outputs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0040: ML Model Inference API Access\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM03: 2025 Supply Chain\",\"mitigation\":\"TLS with pinning; correlate provider request/response IDs; signed webhooks where available; anti-replay nonces; integrity checks on streamed chunks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/S:C\"},{\"id\":101,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Responses may include sensitive training data or echo system prompts that leak into logs/UI.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Output filters/classifiers; redact before persistence; enforce data handling policies; provider assurances on data handling; guardrails to block prompt/system leakage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:R/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N\"},{\"id\":102,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Large or malformed streamed responses exhaust agent parsers/threads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Streaming with backpressure; strict parsers and size/time limits; chunk verification; drop/abort on protocol violations; rate limiting.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H\"}],\"is_final\":true}"
