            "content": "{\"message\":\"Fixes applied: CVSS updated to valid CVSS v4.0 vectors with mandatory SC/SI/SA metrics, replaced invalid UI:R with UI:P, removed deprecated S:C, and adjusted AC:M to AC:H where appropriate. Also cleared potentially unrelated MITRE ATLAS and OWASP LLM categories as flagged. Continuing with remaining items on request.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":1,\"element\":\"User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Attacker spoofs a legitimate user via stolen credentials/session (credential stuffing/phishing) to access accounts.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0012: Valid Accounts\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce MFA; detect and block credential stuffing with rate limits/bot detection; short-lived, rotated session tokens; device binding and re-auth for sensitive actions; session revocation on anomaly.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":2,\"element\":\"User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Users can deny having initiated transactions or requests due to insufficient non-repudiation/audit evidence.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Maintain tamper-evident, time-synced audit logs capturing user ID, IP/device fingerprint, request IDs; digitally sign critical requests/receipts; show confirmation screens and email receipts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":3,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"Session hijacking/fixation or missing CSRF protections allow acting as another user.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Secure, HttpOnly, SameSite=strict cookies; rotate session IDs on login; enforce CSRF tokens; strict origin/referrer checks; JWT audience/issuer/nonce checks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":4,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI) or other input tampering leading to code execution.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable autoescape; never render user-controlled template strings; use Jinja2 sandboxed environment; rigorous input validation/encoding; dependency patching; WAF rules.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":5,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient request/response/audit logging enables denial of actions by users without traceability.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Structured, immutable logs with user/session IDs and request IDs; time sync; write-once or tamper-evident storage; log integrity monitoring.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":6,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"XSS, verbose errors, or misconfigured caching discloses sensitive data.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strict CSP; output encoding; avoid reflecting user input; redact errors; disable client caching of sensitive data; secure headers; template autoescape.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":7,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"Request floods or slowloris exhaust front-end resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"WAF, rate limiting, connection timeouts, keep-alive and header size limits, autoscaling/CDN, request body size limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":8,\"element\":\"Frontend UI (Flask/Jinja2)\",\"threat_description\":\"Template or deserialization flaws enable code execution and privilege escalation on the host.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Disable dangerous Jinja2 features; no untrusted deserialization; run as non-root with seccomp/AppArmor; container isolation; least OS/file permissions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":9,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"JWT forgery/replay (weak secrets, alg=none, missing audience/expiry) allows impersonation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use strong signing (RS256/ES256), verify alg, iss/aud/exp/nbf, jti with replay cache; rotate keys; short TTL; TLS everywhere.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":10,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering via SQL injection during credential checks or JWT tampering in transit.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Parameterize queries via SQLAlchemy; least-privileged DB roles; strict JWT verification; mTLS between services; input validation.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":11,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient login/token issuance logging enables denial of actions and hinders forensics.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Log auth attempts, token issuance/refresh/revocations; correlate with IP/device; store tamper-evidently; alert on anomalies.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":12,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"User enumeration or token/credential leakage via verbose errors or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Generic authentication errors; avoid logging secrets; minimize JWT claims; encrypt secrets at rest; secure config.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":13,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"Brute-force/password spraying and expensive hashing lead to service exhaustion.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limits, CAPTCHA/bot detection, exponential backoff, IP reputation; tune Argon2/bcrypt cost and use adaptive throttling.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":14,\"element\":\"Auth Service (Flask + JWT)\",\"threat_description\":\"Privilege escalation via missing authorization on admin or token scope confusion.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce RBAC/ABAC; validate scopes on every call; default-deny; separate admin surface; security tests for IDOR and scope bypass.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":15,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"Endpoints trust asserted identity (missing JWT verification), allowing impersonation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Verify JWT signature and claims server-side; enforce session binding; check CSRF on state-changing operations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":16,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"Parameter tampering (amounts, IDs) enables fraudulent transactions or metadata corruption.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Server-side validation; enforce object-level auth; idempotency keys; HMAC-signed intents; double-entry checks for funds moves.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":17,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"Insufficient transaction/audit logging lets users repudiate actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Append-only audit trails with request IDs and cryptographic integrity; secure time source; regular log integrity verification.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":18,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"IDOR/over-broad queries disclose other users\u2019 transactions/cards.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce object- and field-level authorization; tenant scoping; parameterized queries; avoid over-fetching; response filtering.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":19,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"Expensive queries/report generation cause CPU/DB exhaustion.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Request quotas; pagination; query timeouts/limits; caching; circuit breakers; backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":20,\"element\":\"Business Logic (Flask)\",\"threat_description\":\"Unsafe eval/deserialization or command execution leads to privilege escalation/RCE.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Avoid eval/exec; no untrusted deserialization; sandbox risky libraries; run with least OS privileges; egress filtering.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":21,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Unauthenticated or mis-scoped upload endpoints allow identity spoofing or cross-tenant writes.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Require auth/authorization on upload; use presigned URLs with short TTL and scope; bind uploads to user/session IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":22,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Path traversal, filename collisions, or malicious file contents tamper with stored data/system.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Normalize/whitelist paths; randomize names; AV/malware scanning; block dangerous types; store outside webroot; checksum verification.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":23,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of upload event logging allows repudiation or inability to trace file origin.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Record uploader identity, timestamps, source IP, file hashes and metadata; store in tamper-evident logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":24,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Serving files without authorization or leaking metadata exposes sensitive content.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private storage; enforce authorization on downloads; presigned short-lived URLs; do not inline sensitive files; encrypt at rest.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":25,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Oversized uploads, zip bombs, or many concurrent uploads exhaust resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Max size limits; streaming uploads; concurrency caps; content inspection; timeouts; detect compression bombs before extraction.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":26,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Vulnerable file parsers (e.g., image/PDF processing) enable code execution and privilege escalation.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0050: Command and Scripting Interpreter\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use patched libraries; isolate processing in sandbox/container with seccomp/AppArmor; drop privileges; limit syscalls and egress.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":27,\"element\":\"Database (PostgreSQL)\",\"threat_description\":\"Data tampering via SQL injection or compromised DB credentials.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strict ORM parameterization; least-privileged roles; separate read/write users; change control; DB ACLs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":28,\"element\":\"Database (PostgreSQL)\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of immutable audit trails allows repudiation of DB changes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable pg_audit; append-only audit schema; WAL archiving; cryptographic log sealing and offsite replication.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":29,\"element\":\"Database (PostgreSQL)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data exposure via misconfigurations, backups, or snapshot leaks.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Encrypt at rest and in transit; restrict backup access; row-level security; data masking; secrets management.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":30,\"element\":\"Database (PostgreSQL)\",\"threat_description\":\"DB resource exhaustion (locks, long-running queries) causing service degradation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Connection pooling; query timeouts; statement time limits; indexes; load shedding; monitoring and auto-kill of runaway queries.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":31,\"element\":\"Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Files altered or deleted (ransomware/insider) corrupting content.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0025: Exfiltration via Cyber Means\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Immutable/WORM or versioned storage; checksums; restricted service accounts; signed writes; backup/restore testing.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":32,\"element\":\"Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"No provenance/versioning allows repudiation of file changes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enable object versioning; maintain write logs with hashes and timestamps; tamper-evident storage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:H/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":33,\"element\":\"Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Publicly exposed storage paths or weak ACLs leak uploaded files.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private buckets/paths; deny-by-default ACLs; encrypt at rest; no direct public links; presigned short-lived URLs for access.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":34,\"element\":\"Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Storage exhaustion or I/O saturation prevents reads/writes.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Store\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Quotas; lifecycle policies; monitoring/alerts; separate hot/cold tiers; autoscaling and backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":35,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Impersonation of downstream LLM endpoint or caller identity leads to unauthorized access/actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS with certificate pinning to provider; domain allowlists/DNSSEC; request signing; workload identity for outbound calls; strict inbound authn/z.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":36,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompt injection via user-controlled inputs causes the agent to exfiltrate data or perform unsafe actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Input isolation and schema validation; content/URL allowlists; retrieval/attachment sanitization; instruction hierarchy and output filters; tool/function allowlists.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":37,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Lack of prompt/response/tool-use logging enables repudiation and hinders incident response.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Structured logs linking user, context, prompts, responses, and tool calls; PII minimization/redaction; tamper-evident storage; retention policies.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":38,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive information disclosure in prompts or outputs, including system prompt leakage.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"PII scrubbing/redaction; never include secrets in prompts; encrypt context at rest/in transit; detect and block leakage; mask system prompts; retrieval access controls.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":39,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Unbounded LLM calls or large contexts cause cost blowups or service exhaustion.\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Per-user/org quotas; rate limits; circuit breakers; response caching; max tokens/context; upstream budget caps and alerts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":40,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Excessive agency or insecure tool plugins allow escalation to privileged actions (confused-deputy).\",\"element_type\":\"Process\",\"stride\":\"Elevation of Privileges\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0053: LLM Plugin Compromise\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM06: 2025 Excessive Agency\",\"mitigation\":\"Capability sandboxing; explicit allowlists; human-in-the-loop for high-risk actions; per-tool scopes/guardrails; egress and secret access controls.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":41,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"Spoofed provider endpoint or SDK/update compromise leads to adversary-controlled responses.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Spoofing\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0010: ML Supply Chain Compromise\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Use official SDKs with signature verification; pin TLS certificates; verify domains; monitor SBOM/attestations; restrict outbound to allowlisted hosts.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":42,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"Provider denies generating a harmful output or request receipt due to lack of traceability.\",\"element_type\":\"External Entity\",\"stride\":\"Repudiation\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Capture request IDs, timestamps, hashes of prompts/responses; enable provider-side logging/correlation; contractual SLAs for auditability.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:L/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":43,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Request tampering/MITM or client-side manipulation of parameters and CSRF leading to unauthorized actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS 1.3 + HSTS; CSRF tokens; server-side validation/authorization; avoid sensitive data in URLs; integrity/checksums for critical intents.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":44,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Sniffing or leakage of credentials/PII via insecure transport, referer headers, or browser cache.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce TLS/HSTS; secure headers (Referrer-Policy=no-referrer, Cache-Control=no-store); avoid PII in query strings; input redaction in logs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":45,\"element\":\"User (Browser) -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Request floods or large bodies overwhelm front-end and upstream services.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"WAF/rate limits; request body size/time limits; bot detection; CDN shielding; connection throttling/backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":46,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering/MITM or content injection modifies outputs (e.g., malicious JS).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS/HSTS; strong CSP; subresource integrity; avoid inline scripts; response signing where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":47,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data exposed in responses or via client/proxy caching and verbose errors.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0049: Exploit Public-Facing Application\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Minimize sensitive fields; redact errors; Cache-Control: no-store; X-Content-Type-Options; avoid exposing internal IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":48,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> User (Browser)\",\"threat_description\":\"Large/streaming responses and downloads saturate client/network, amplifying DoS.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-response size/time limits; pagination/chunking; compression and rate limits; abort slow clients.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":49,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with login/register payloads or MITM on internal hop alters auth decisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS/service mesh; request signing; strict schema validation; replay protection (nonce/jti).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":50,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Credentials or PII disclosure over the wire or through logs/metrics.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; minimize/avoid transmitting secrets; redact logs; secure metrics; OAuth best practices.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":51,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst of auth requests exhausts the service on this path.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-IP/user rate limits at edge; CAPTCHA; circuit breakers; priority queues for authenticated traffic.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":52,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token/session tampering or swap in transit (e.g., man-in-the-middle inside cluster).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; Set-Cookie with HttpOnly/Secure/SameSite=strict; sign tokens (RS/ES); bind token to client context where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":53,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token/session disclosure via headers, referrers, or improper storage.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Do not place tokens in URLs; HttpOnly cookies; Referrer-Policy: no-referrer; avoid localStorage for secrets; short TTL.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":54,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Token refresh/issuance bursts overwhelm channels or caches.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Throttle token issuance; exponential backoff; cache headers; staggered refresh; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":55,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with DB connection/queries in transit (downgraded TLS, MITM).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Enforce TLS to DB with cert validation; restrict network paths; parameterized queries; least-privileged DB user.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":56,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of credentials or password hashes during auth checks.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; avoid SELECTing sensitive columns; hash-and-compare within DB function; encrypt columns; protect backups/snapshots.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":57,\"element\":\"Auth Service -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Auth check bursts exhaust DB connections or locks.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Connection pooling; rate limit login attempts; statement_timeout; caching of safe-to-cache metadata.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":58,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Validation responses altered in transit causing incorrect auth results.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; response schema validation; check row counts/expected flags; replay protection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":59,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of unnecessary columns in responses (e.g., password hashes, salts).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Principle of least data; views/stored procedures; column-level encryption/masking; avoid logging result sets.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":60,\"element\":\"Database -> Auth Service\",\"threat_description\":\"Slow/large responses tie up threads and block auth pipeline.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Query optimization; pagination; timeouts; circuit breaker fallback to \u2018temporarily unavailable\u2019.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"}],\"is_final\":false}"
        },
        {
            "role": "user",
            "content": "**CONTINUE**"
        },
        {
            "role": "assistant",
            "content": "{\"message\":\"Applied fixes for items 61\u2013102: corrected CVSS v4.0 vectors (added mandatory SC/SI/SA, replaced UI:R with UI:P, replaced AC:M with AC:H, removed v3 scope S:C), and removed flagged potentially unrelated MITRE ATLAS/OWASP LLM categories. Let me know if you want me to prioritize risks next.\",\"threats\":[{\"id\":61,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Parameter tampering or JWT misuse in transit leads to unauthorized actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; verify JWTs; server-side validation; idempotency keys for state changes; signed requests for critical actions.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":62,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Leakage of PII or account identifiers via headers, URLs, or logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; avoid PII in URL; structured logging with redaction; encrypt sensitive request fields end-to-end where feasible.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":63,\"element\":\"Frontend UI -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"High rate of state-changing actions overwhelms business logic.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-user/org quotas; rate limiting; asynchronous job offloading; backpressure/circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":64,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering in transit could alter balances/transactions shown.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; signed data for critical reads; ETag integrity; client-side verification for critical displays if applicable.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":65,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Over-broad data in responses discloses other users\u2019 info (multi-tenant leakage).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Data minimization; object/tenant scoping; response filtering; schema-based serializers with allowlists.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":66,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Frontend UI\",\"threat_description\":\"Very large responses or server-sent events overwhelm clients and infrastructure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Pagination; max response size and time; streaming with backpressure; per-client rate limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":67,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with SQL traffic or parameters over the network leads to incorrect writes/reads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS to DB; prepared statements; role separation; firewall rules limiting DB access to service IPs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":68,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of sensitive query parameters or embedded secrets (e.g., in DSNs).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Secrets manager for DSNs; TLS; minimize PII in queries; log redaction; encrypt sensitive columns.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":69,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Query storms or long transactions overload DB via this path.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Statement timeouts; connection pool limits; caching; rate limits; circuit breakers/fail fast.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":70,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered result sets (MITM) or stale replays lead to incorrect business decisions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; response verification (row counts, checksums); reject unexpected schemas; use transaction IDs.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":71,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Excess or sensitive fields returned leak PII/PCI data to app and logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Views/whitelists; row/column-level security; data masking; restrict ORM eager loading; log redaction.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":72,\"element\":\"Database -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Huge result sets overwhelm app memory/threads causing cascade failures.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"LIMIT/pagination; server-side cursors; memory limits; streaming with backpressure.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":73,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with upload metadata (e.g., content-type, filename) changes downstream handling.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Strict schema; sanitize filenames; sign metadata (HMAC) with request; enforce server-detected MIME types.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":74,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of sensitive metadata (filenames, paths, user IDs) during upload initiation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; minimize metadata; avoid embedding PII in names; log redaction; encrypt sensitive metadata fields in transit and at rest.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":75,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Oversized or too many concurrent upload requests overwhelm the handler.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Max body size; streaming; concurrency caps; per-user quotas; pre-signed URL expirations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":76,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Status/metadata tampering (e.g., false success) misleads business logic.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; signed callbacks with shared keys; correlate with server-side computed hashes and sizes; idempotency tokens.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":77,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Metadata responses leak sensitive attributes (owner IDs, internal paths).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Minimize response fields; mask IDs; access checks before returning metadata; log redaction.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":78,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst of callback/status messages overloads business logic message handlers.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Rate limiting; queueing with backpressure; collapse duplicate callbacks; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":79,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering of binary data or headers in transit to storage (e.g., NFS/S3 MITM).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS to object store; server-side encryption with customer-managed keys; checksum/ETag verification; signed URLs with short TTL.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":80,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"Exposure of file contents or keys during upload (e.g., misconfigured bucket, sniffing).\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Private buckets/shares; TLS; server-side encryption; tight IAM; disable public ACLs; VPC endpoints.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":81,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Local File Storage\",\"threat_description\":\"High-rate or large uploads saturate storage bandwidth/IO.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Per-tenant quotas; bandwidth throttling; multipart/chunked uploads with limits; lifecycle policies to free space.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":82,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered confirmations (e.g., fake ETag) or replays mislead about write success.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; verify ETag/checksum vs. local hash; ensure strong consistency or read-after-write checks; nonce-based replay protection.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":83,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Path, bucket, or internal IDs exposed in confirmations/logs leak structure.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Return opaque IDs; avoid logging full paths; encrypt sensitive metadata; strict IAM to prevent listing.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:L/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":84,\"element\":\"Local File Storage -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Delayed or streaming confirmations hold connections open and exhaust handler threads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Async callbacks; timeouts; bounded thread pools; bulk confirmations.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":85,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering with metadata inserts or parameters in transit to DB.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"mTLS; prepared statements; input normalization; least-privilege DB role for writes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":86,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive metadata (PII, file hashes) exposed during insert or in logs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; encrypt sensitive columns; minimize stored metadata; redaction; access controls on logs/backups.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":87,\"element\":\"File Upload Handler -> Database\",\"threat_description\":\"High-volume insert traffic saturates DB write capacity.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Batching; async queues; write quotas; partitioning/indexing; circuit breakers on spikes.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":88,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampered insert confirmations cause inconsistent application state.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS; verify row counts/IDs; idempotent operations; compare echoed values with request.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":89,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Disclosure of internal keys/paths or unrelated rows in confirmation payloads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Views limiting columns; DTO/serializer allowlists; masking; logging hygiene.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":90,\"element\":\"Database -> File Upload Handler\",\"threat_description\":\"Slow confirmations/backpressure cause upload handler thread starvation.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"Timeouts; async processing; bounded queues; fallback retries with jitter.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:H/AT:N/PR:L/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":91,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Prompt injection rides along user context to alter downstream agent instructions/actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0051: LLM Prompt Injection\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM01: 2025 Prompt Injection\",\"mitigation\":\"Isolate untrusted content; instruction hierarchy; input schema and content filters; tool/function allowlists; strip/escape model-affecting tokens in content.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":92,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Sensitive data or system prompts included in context leak to the agent and potentially to the model/provider.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Redact/minimize context; never include secrets; role-based retrieval; mask/rotate system prompts; encrypt sensitive context at rest/in transit.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":93,\"element\":\"Business Logic -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Huge contexts or high request rate overwhelm the agent pipeline and budgets.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Max tokens/context; per-user quotas; circuit breakers; deduplication/caching; admission control.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":94,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Response tampering or tool-use injection embedded in model outputs leads to unsafe downstream actions.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM05: 2025 Improper Output Handling\",\"mitigation\":\"Treat outputs as untrusted; schema/regex validators; require human-in-the-loop for high-risk actions; allowlist tools; strip control tokens.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":95,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"AI responses may contain sensitive data or system instructions that leak when logged or shown.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"PII redaction before logging/display; classify and filter outputs; least-privilege access to logs/telemetry; data retention limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":96,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> Business Logic\",\"threat_description\":\"Large outputs or streaming tokens overwhelm parsers/UI and backend resources.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0034: Cost Harvesting\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Max tokens in response; streaming with backpressure; timeouts; chunk validation and truncation; rate limits.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":97,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"MITM/tampering of AI requests alters prompts, tools, or parameters across the Internet boundary.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS 1.3 with cert pinning; DNSSEC/DoH; egress allowlists; request signing and nonce; verify provider hostnames.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":98,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"PII/secrets in prompts exfiltrated to provider via inference API.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0024: Exfiltration via ML Inference API\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Data minimization/redaction; per-tenant consent and DPA; encrypt prompts in transit; segregate contexts; use provider data controls (no-train flags).\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":99,\"element\":\"AI Support Agent -> DeepSeek LLM\",\"threat_description\":\"Burst or expensive requests (long contexts/high compute) cause DoS/cost blowouts.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Token and RPM quotas; budget caps and alerts; exponential backoff with jitter; cache identical prompts; circuit breakers.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":100,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Tampering/replay of AI responses or upstream gateway injection alters outputs.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Tampering\",\"mitre_atlas\":null,\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":null,\"mitigation\":\"TLS with pinning; correlate provider request/response IDs; signed webhooks where available; anti-replay nonces; integrity checks on streamed chunks.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:H/VI:H/VA:L/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":101,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Responses may include sensitive training data or echo system prompts that leak into logs/UI.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Information Disclosure\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0057: LLM Data Leakage\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM02: 2025 Sensitive Information Disclosure\",\"mitigation\":\"Output filters/classifiers; redact before persistence; enforce data handling policies; provider assurances on data handling; guardrails to block prompt/system leakage.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:P/VC:H/VI:N/VA:N/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"},{\"id\":102,\"element\":\"DeepSeek LLM -> AI Support Agent\",\"threat_description\":\"Large or malformed streamed responses exhaust agent parsers/threads.\",\"element_type\":\"Data Flow\",\"stride\":\"Denial of Service\",\"mitre_atlas\":\"AML.T0029: Denial of ML Service\",\"owasp_top_10_for_llm\":\"LLM10: 2025 Unbounded Consumption\",\"mitigation\":\"Streaming with backpressure; strict parsers and size/time limits; chunk verification; drop/abort on protocol violations; rate limiting.\",\"cvss_vector\":\"CVSS:4.0/AV:N/AC:L/AT:N/PR:N/UI:N/VC:N/VI:N/VA:H/SC:N/SI:N/SA:N\"}],\"is_final\":true}"
        }
    ]
}